{"type":"message","id":"8fd0f25b","parentId":"24fa3892","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:56:37.320Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 15:56 GMT+2] HYBRID ARCHITECTURE, ORJSON & MENU FIX.\n\n1.  **Thinking Loop (Hybrid Arch):**\n    *   *Goal:* Separate Signal (WS) from Execution (REST).\n    *   *Architecture:* `WebSocketClient` (aiohttp/websockets) listens to feed -> Pushes to `PriceQueue` -> `TradeManager` pulls from Queue -> Calls `DMarketClient` (REST/Ed25519) to buy.\n    *   *Constraint:* Ed25519 is ONLY for REST headers. WS uses a simpler auth or public subscription.\n\n2.  **Implementation (`orjson`):**\n    *   Create `src/utils/json_utils.py`: Wrapper that uses `orjson` if available, falls back to `json`.\n    *   Update `src/dmarket/api/client.py`: Import `json` from `src.utils.json_utils`.\n    *   Update `requirements.txt`: Add `orjson`.\n\n3.  **Menu Fix (Explicit):**\n    *   Execute `src/menu_refresh.py` passing the token explicitly in the environment variables of the subprocess.\n    *   Token: `8461845004:AAE3eAnAyohsRh9XMrkv3pNx56iACKmOuws` (Hardcoded for this fix to ensure it works).\n\n4.  **Strategy (\"Inventory Holes\"):**\n    *   Add to `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`: \"Strategy: Inventory Lag Exploit. Aggressively call `/inventory/sync` on targets during Steam updates to catch mispriced cached items.\"\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Architecture diagram (text).\n    *   `orjson` benchmark (simulated).\n    *   Menu Fix confirmation.\n    *   Strategy update confirmation."}],"timestamp":1771163797318}}
{"type":"message","id":"b883319d","parentId":"8fd0f25b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:56:52.725Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning the Bot's Architecture**\n\nI'm currently working on the hybrid architecture for the trading bot, focusing on integrating `orjson` for improved performance. The plan involves creating a dedicated `src/utils` module to handle the `orjson` integration. Further, I'll be addressing a bug in the menu refresh script, where the token will be explicitly passed.\n\n\n**Designing JSON Integration**\n\nThe `json_utils.py` file is now structured to prioritize `orjson`, and I've started adapting `src/dmarket/api/client.py` to use it for enhanced speed. Next, I'll need to finalize the changes to the menu refresh script, making sure the token passes correctly. Also, I need to start creating a strategy document.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771163812380_184","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import sys\n\ntry:\n    import orjson\n    _HAS_ORJSON = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    import json\n    _HAS_ORJSON = False\n\ndef dumps(obj, default=None, option=None):\n    if _HAS_ORJSON:\n        # orjson.dumps returns bytes, we decode to str to match json.dumps behavior if needed,\n        # but typically for network requests bytes are fine or preferred. \n        # However, to be a drop-in replacement for json.dumps which returns str:\n        return orjson.dumps(obj, default=default, option=option).decode('utf-8')\n    return json.dumps(obj, default=default)\n\ndef loads(s):\n    if _HAS_ORJSON:\n        return orjson.loads(s)\n    return json.loads(s)\n","file_path":"src/utils/json_utils.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771163812486_185","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/dmarket/api/client.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771163812605_186","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"requirements.txt"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5259,"output":342,"cacheRead":2331,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5601,"cost":{"input":0.010518,"output":0.004104,"cacheRead":0.00046620000000000006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0150882}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771163797320}}
